# Google Gemini API Key - Get from Google Cloud Console
#Step-by-step:
#1.Visit Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
#2.Click on the project dropdown (top-left corner near the Google Cloud logo).
#3.Click “New Project”.
#4.Enter project details:Project name: AI Flow Gemini Key or anything you like.
#5.Leave the organization as-is (or No organization if you're using a personal account).
#6.Click “Create”.
#7.After creation, go to https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#8.Click “Create API key” again. Now you should see your newly created project listed.
#9.Select it → Proceed → Copy the key → Use it in your .env
VITE_APP_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key

# Supabase project credentials
#Used if your app stores user data, history, auth, etc. in Supabase (a Firebase alternative)
#How to get:
#1.Go to https://supabase.com/
#2.Create a new project
#3.Once inside the project, go to Project Settings → API
#4.You’ll find:URL = VITE_SUPABASE_URL and anon public API key = VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# Backend API
#copy this as-is
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Google Analytics 
#Go to https://analytics.google.com/
# Step-by-step:
#1.Login → Click Admin (bottom-left gear icon).
#2.Under "Account" → Click Create Account (if you don’t have one).
#3.Under "Property" → Click Create Property.
#4.Fill in:Name: AI Flow Analytics;Time zone, currency → Click Next;Choose your business size & goals → Click Create;Choose platform: Web
#5.Enter:Website URL (https://ai-flow-gssoc.vercel.app/);Stream name (e.g., ai-flow-gssoc)
#6.Click Create Stream
#7.Copy the Measurement ID:You’ll get something like:G-XXXXXXXXXX ;Put that in your .env:
VITE_APP_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=your_ga_id

# Blogger API 
#  Step-by-Step to Get Blogger API Key:
# 1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create or select a project.
# 3. In the left sidebar → Go to "APIs & Services" → "Library".
# 4. Search for **Blogger API v3** and click "Enable".
# 5. Now go to: "APIs & Services" → "Credentials".
# 6. Click "Create Credentials" → Choose **API Key**.
# 7. Copy the generated API key.

# Step-by-Step to Get Blog ID:
# 1. Go to your blog: https://www.blogger.com/
# 2. Open your blog dashboard.
# 3. In the URL bar, find the **Blog ID** 
#    Example: If the URL is:
#    https://www.blogger.com/blog/posts/1234567890123456789
#    Then your blog ID is: 1234567890123456789
# Paste both below:
VITE_BLOGGER_API_KEY=your_blogger_api_key
VITE_BLOG_ID=your_blog_id



